  "prompt": "Is there an online calculator that shows work?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several online calculators that show work step-by-step. Here are a few popular options:\n\n1. **Symbolab**: This calculator provides detailed step-by-step solutions for a wide range of mathematical problems, including algebra, calculus, trigonometry, and more.\n\n2. **Mathway**: Mathway offers step-by-step solutions to various math problems, from basic arithmetic to advanced calculus. It also covers chemistry, physics, and engineering problems.\n\n3. **Wolfram Alpha**: Wolfram Alpha is a computational engine that can solve many types of problems and show the steps involved in arriving at the solution.\n\n4. **Desmos**: Primarily known as an online graphing calculator, Desmos also provides step-by-step solutions and explanations for specific types of equations and inequalities.\n\nThese tools can be very helpful for understanding the underlying processes and methods used to solve different types of problems.",
